OL,4,Cabout subpostmasters 'sniffing around'
OL,6,FAsked if he knew the Post Office
OL,7,Fhelpline was deterring subpostmasters
OL,8,Fby telling them to make up shortfalls
OL,9,Fin their accounts on their own, Mr
OL,10,FThomson told the inquiry: "Myself or
OL,11,Fsome of the team would be aware of
OL,12,Fthat, without a doubt."
OL,14,FSam Stein KC, on behalf of a number of
OL,15,Fsubpostmasters, asked Mr Thomson if it
OL,16,Fwas fair to say he "got into the Post
OL,17,FOffice bed with Paula Vennells and did
OL,18,Fwhatever she wanted you to do", to
OL,19,Fwhich he replied: "It's nonsense."
