OL,6,FMr Thomson said it had taken "a lot of
OL,7,Fbadgering" of then-Post Office chief
OL,8,Fexecutive Paula Vennells to agree to
OL,9,Fthe deal, and that her team "would
OL,10,Fhave preferred the NFSP withered on
OL,11,Fthe vine".
OL,13,FPut to him by Mr Blake that they were
OL,14,Fsignificant figures, Mr Thomson told
OL,15,Fthe inquiry the NFSP "took on new
OL,16,Ffunctions" as part of the agreement.
